Seriously - I agree that (besides DKP which don't work for open raids) it's probably the best and only system that works, but here's just another case of abuse that makes people's faith in the system weaken.<br>
<br>
NBG isn't about trying to see if you can rationalize a tiny bit of need so you can get in on an item, it's about thinking &quot;Hmm, if I win this item, will I be F-ing over classes or players that could use this item better than me?&quot;. Rolling on a big INT or WIS item to raise your skills is total BS, but since it's hybrid only, it really doesn't matter (except I heard they added Beastlord as a useable class on the Torque which would make thsy an instant BST award every time, but can't verify that change). If an Eyepatch dropped on a Vox raid and any non-caster classes tried to roll (yes, I mean PAL, SHD, RNG and whatever) I would have a serious problem with that no matter what screwed up reasoning they presented as to why they &quot;absolutely needed&quot; that +INT +WIS item over the needs of casters.<br>
<br>
Kinda like someone rolling on a Berserker's BP when they have a Vindi BP so they can complete their fashion collection.<br>
